(
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BEAE7A70C96DFBA1" box="[159,285,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Figs. 1a–h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BF187A70C948FBA1" box="[297,312,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1011,1035]" captionTargetBox="[414,1213,225,995]" captionTargetId="figure-131@15.[358,1232,225,995]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution map of species belonging to the Macrostomus ferrugineus species-group with tergite 8 acute distally. Symbols represent the known collection localities as follows: solid circle = M. fuscithorax, n. sp.; square = M. fusciventris,, n. sp.; solid triangle = M. melanothorax, n. sp.; open circle = M. ferrugineus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795BFF97BEA67AA7CBAFFAC2" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795BFF97BEA67AA7CBAFFAC2" blockId="2.[151,1436,1202,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795BFF97BEA67AA7C96BFB12" bold="true" box="[151,283,1202,1228]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax and abdomen shining black, legs predominantly yellow; postcranium black with gray pruinescence; male tergite 8 acute distally; vein CuA 
<subScript id="179EF00C795BFF97BD357AFCCB7CFB29" attach="left" box="[772,780,1257,1271]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">1</subScript>
shorter than dm-cu vein. Female without pinnate scales on hind tibia; wing approximately as wide as male wing, rather hyaline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795BFF97BEF47B3CCB27F806" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795BFF97BEF47B3CCA02F92E" blockId="2.[151,1436,1202,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795BFF97BEF47B3CC92FFA9D" bold="true" box="[197,351,1321,1347]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54A14CEB795BFF97BF597B3CC9A7FA9D" box="[360,471,1321,1347]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Frons approximately one third anterior ocellus width. Face slightly wider than frons only at ventral margin. Postcranium entirely black. Antennae lost. Palpus brown. Thorax shining black with gray-brown pruinescence more distinct on disc of scutum. Setae: 4 dorsocentrals; 1 supra-alar presutural; scutellar lost; 3–5 antepronotals; 1–3 tiny proepisternals; 3–5 katatergitals. Legs (only hind leg present) yellow with distal tarsomeres 3–5 or 4–5 brown; hind tibia with one distal slender setae; first hind tarsomere with no slender setae dorsally. Wing with pterostigma brown and distal patch slightly brown infuscated (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BF117804C904F9F5" box="[288,372,1553,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Halter with stem light yellow, knob partially brown. CuA 
<subScript id="179EF00C795BFF97BA007834CC49F9F1" attach="left" box="[1073,1081,1569,1583]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">1</subScript>
vein shorter than dm-cu vein. Abdomen shining black. Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BC61782ECAD9F98B" box="[592,681,1595,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
) with a thin distal projection. Epandrium with posterodorsal protuberance slightly longer than anterodorsal protuberance (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BD5F7877CBB3F9A2" box="[878,963,1634,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). Anterior cercus rather short; posterior cercus with many anterodorsal and slender dorsal setae and a internal small distinct ramification (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BB05789DCDFDF97C" box="[1332,1421,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BF0C78BAC9E0F917" box="[317,400,1711,1737]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
) with a few setae medially, a paired rounded and relatively wide protuberance distally, and an acute subapical process medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795BFF97BEF478E9CA8AF8C8" blockId="2.[151,1436,1202,2008]" box="[197,762,1788,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Size. Body length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC795BFF97BFAC78E9C98AF8C8" box="[413,506,1788,1814]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC795BFF97BCA978E9CA86F8C8" box="[664,758,1788,1814]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795BFF97BEF47936CB98F854" blockId="2.[151,1436,1202,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Female. Frons approximately anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately half anterior ocellus width. Legs without pinnate scales. Tergite and sternite 8 (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BD90795FCC6AF8BA" box="[929,1050,1866,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Figs. 1f–g</figureCitation>
) as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795BFF97BADC795FCDECF8BD" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1261,1436,1866,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795BFF97BADC795FCDECF8BD" box="[1261,1436,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. Genital fork (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC795BFF97BFD77965CA4AF854" box="[486,570,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1386,1410]" captionTargetBox="[196,1381,191,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-275@3.[151,1436,140,1400]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macrostomus fuscithorax, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing apex; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, epandrium and cercus, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–H: female. F, Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; G, sternite 8, ventral view; H, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: DP, distal protuberance; SP, subapical process. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B–G = 0.2 mm; H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 1h</figureCitation>
) with well sclerotized T-shaped rod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795BFF97BEF47982CA8AF86F" blockId="2.[151,1436,1202,2008]" box="[197,762,1943,1969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Size. Body length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC795BFF97BFAC7982C98AF86F" box="[413,506,1943,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
