<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795AFF96BEF47958CC1CF8B9" box="[197,1132,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795AFF96BEF47958CC1CF8B9" blockId="3.[151,1436,1560,2011]" box="[197,1132,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BEF47958C922F8B9" bold="true" box="[197,338,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BFD47958CA5EF8B8" box="[485,558,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">fuscus</emphasis>
= black in reference to the black color of thorax.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300A1C2795AFF91BEF47966CC9BFEDC" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA5F249795AFF91BEF47966CC9BFEDC" blockId="3.[151,1436,1560,2011]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,258]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BEF47966C920F853" bold="true" box="[197,336,1907,1933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BF697961CAF2F853" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[344,642,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BF697961CAF2F853" box="[344,642,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Macrostomus fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BCA07966CAA4F853" bold="true" box="[657,724,1907,1933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795AFF96BCA07966CAA4F853" box="[657,724,1907,1933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BDAE7961CCA9F850" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[927,1241,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BDAE7961CC3EF853" box="[927,1102,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BAD77961CDE4F853" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1254,1428,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BAD77961CDE4F853" box="[1254,1428,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">M. fusciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BEA6798FC8ACF86A" bold="true" box="[151,220,1946,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795AFF96BEA6798FC8ACF86A" box="[151,220,1946,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BF28798EC99AF86A" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[281,490,1947,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BF28798EC99AF86A" box="[281,490,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">M. melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BFCA798FCA30F86A" bold="true" box="[507,576,1946,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D9320795AFF96BFCA798FCA30F86A" box="[507,576,1946,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
on the basis of the shape of male tergite 8, which is acutely projected distally. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BECC79D4CA5EF804" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[253,558,1985,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BECC79D4CA5EF804" box="[253,558,1985,2010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Macrostomus fuscithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a black thorax with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF96BD4D79D4CC3AF804" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[892,1098,1985,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF96BD4D79D4CC3AF804" box="[892,1098,1985,2010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">M. melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795AFF91BB4D79D4C96EFF6F" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795AFF91BB4D79D4C96EFF6F" italics="true" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group have a predominantly yellow thorax. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA795DFF91BA1F7E8DCC88FF6F" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1070,1272,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B795DFF91BA1F7E8DCC88FF6F" box="[1070,1272,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">M. melanothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by vein CuA 
<subScript id="179EF00C795DFF91BBA57EBDCDECFF68" attach="right" box="[1428,1436,168,182]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">1</subScript>
being shorter than vein dm-cu, by the shape of posterior cercus, the apex of the hypandrium, and by the epandrium with the posterodorsal protuberance slightly longer than anterodorsal protuberance.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
